Bariis Iskukaris (Somali style rice)

Xawaash:
1 tbsp cumin seeds
1 tbsp coriander seeds
2 tsp dried whole sage
1 tsp black peppercorns
1 tsp fenugreek seeds
1 tsp ground tumeric
1 1/4 tsp ground ginger
8 green cardamom pods
10 whole cloves
1/4 tsp freshly grated nutmeg
1/3 cinnamon stick

Combine all the spices in a spice grinder and finely grind. Set aside.

Topping:
2 tbsp olive oil
1 red onion, peeled and thinly sliced
1/4 c raisins
1 red bell pepper, cored and thinly sliced
salt

Heat olive oil in a wide, deep pot over medium high heat and add the onions, stirring occasionally until translucent. Add raisins and allow to soften, ~2 min, then add red bell pepper and cook until softened, ~5-7 min. Season with salt and set aside on a paper towel.

Rice:
4 c basmati rice
1/2 c olive oil
1 large yellow onion, chopped
3 cloves garlic, minced
2 cinnamon sticks
5 whole green cardamom pods
10 whole cloves
2 tsp xawaash spice mix
8 c chicken stock
1 tsp saffron threads, finely chopped
1 c raisins
salt

Soak rice in cold water 30-45 min, then drain. In same pot, make the rice. Heat 1/2 c oil. Add onions and saute, stirring frequently, until softened, 6-8 min. Add garlic, cinnamon sticks, cardamom, cloves, and xawaash and cook, stirring, 1 min. Stir in stock and rice. Bring to a boil, then cover and cook on low heat, 20 min. Stir in saffron and raisins and season to taste with salt. Cover, turn off heat and steam for 5 more min. Transfer to a serving platter. Sprinkle topping over rice and serve.
